01:16:29.117 --> 01:16:32.450
Look at me, please. Look at me.
Please, Lara, look at me.

01:16:33.388 --> 01:16:36.846
I love you. I do.
Do you love me?

01:16:41.430 --> 01:16:42.897
I thought you were dead!

01:16:43.765 --> 01:16:47.394
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

01:17:00.048 --> 01:17:01.140
Come here.

01:17:05.487 --> 01:17:07.045
That's it, eh?
Come here.

01:17:10.692 --> 01:17:14.219
I'm taking you to Scotland, that's it.
I'm just going to take you and leave.

01:17:14.262 --> 01:17:16.321
we're going to get away from
all this political shit.

01:17:18.333 --> 01:17:21.063
You're never going to leave the lRA.

01:17:21.103 --> 01:17:24.834
Oh, no? I'll do whatever you want me
to do at this point. I'm yours.

01:17:25.641 --> 01:17:30.078
Because you're captured by the anarchy
of it all, like the rest of them.

01:17:30.646 --> 01:17:31.943
And you love it.

01:17:35.083 --> 01:17:38.109
So we're going to hit the pub afterwards,
courtesy of the Libyan government.

01:17:38.186 --> 01:17:40.177
Don't go AwOL again.
It's not healthy.

01:17:40.722 --> 01:17:42.952
I am in charge
of this entire operation.

01:17:44.393 --> 01:17:45.883
Anyway, look, I've got to get back.

01:17:45.994 --> 01:17:48.258
Like, Lara's not exactly
buying my excuses anymore.

01:17:48.296 --> 01:17:50.856
Yeah, I was married to a nice girl once.
She hung in there until l...

01:17:50.932 --> 01:17:53.400
until I tried
the alien abduction excuse.

01:17:53.969 --> 01:17:55.960
what's this, the "take care
of your family" speech?

01:17:56.104 --> 01:17:58.800
Hey, you're so young, Martin,
you make me envious.

01:17:58.840 --> 01:18:02.435
Life's full of mistakes. I lost
my family making all the obvious ones.

01:18:03.845 --> 01:18:05.676
There, that was your speech.

01:18:06.848 --> 01:18:07.906
Aye, very moving.

01:18:09.484 --> 01:18:12.180
what are you saying? Are you saying
that I should quit? Is that it?

01:18:12.220 --> 01:18:14.484
-we've had a good run.
-Aye, yeah, we have.

01:18:16.491 --> 01:18:20.257
Look, there's going to be a drop.
It's on Thursday night, on the docks.

01:18:20.328 --> 01:18:23.491
My mate's wee brother's going to be
there. Don't worry about him.

01:18:23.598 --> 01:18:26.920
He doesn't know anything.
He's just going to be there, all right?

01:18:26.968 --> 01:18:30.426
So leave him alone.
Go in, get the guns, and then get out.

01:18:32.040 --> 01:18:33.268
Okay. This is it.

01:18:34.876 --> 01:18:35.865
what the fuck's going on?

01:18:35.877 --> 01:18:37.003
Get down on the ground!

01:18:38.046 --> 01:18:38.842
what's going on?

01:18:39.414 --> 01:18:42.212
Ah, Jesus Christ.
Marty, they're Brits.

01:18:47.155 --> 01:18:49.123
Get it started. Get the fuck out
of here, come on.

01:18:50.992 --> 01:18:52.755
what the fuck was that all about?

01:19:03.805 --> 01:19:06.273
You said I'd save lives, right,
and that includes my people...

01:19:06.341 --> 01:19:07.365
you Brit bastard!

01:19:07.442 --> 01:19:10.070
It's a set-up for a bigger fish.
It was out of my hands.

01:19:10.178 --> 01:19:12.146
It's big boys' rules
you're playing here!

01:19:12.180 --> 01:19:13.511
"Big boys' rules," is that it, right?

01:19:13.615 --> 01:19:15.583
You're going to hide behind
"big boys' rules"?

01:19:15.650 --> 01:19:17.709
Okay, well, how about this?
Like, "Yes, sir,"' huh?

01:19:17.819 --> 01:19:20.845
"Consider it done, sir!
He's just another statistic, sir!

01:19:20.922 --> 01:19:22.549
It didn't even happen, sir!"

01:19:23.558 --> 01:19:24.252
Right?

01:19:25.093 --> 01:19:27.288
You think that shit is going
to change the fact that you...

01:19:27.329 --> 01:19:32.357
yeah, you... you killed an 18-year
old fellow who didn't know any better?

01:19:34.035 --> 01:19:35.195
And you're innocent?

01:19:36.104 --> 01:19:39.471
You and your mates are volunteers
in a volunteer organization.

01:19:40.942 --> 01:19:43.502
who's making any one of you do anything
you don't want to do?

01:19:43.545 --> 01:19:45.445
where does that leave you
and your mates?

01:19:46.848 --> 01:19:48.941
Aye... Aye, my mates.

01:19:49.851 --> 01:19:51.953
That's exactly what they are,
they're my mates.

01:19:51.953 --> 01:19:54.513
You know, I know his ma.
All right, do you understand that?

01:19:54.589 --> 01:19:56.819
Is that getting through?
I know this guy's ma...

01:19:56.925 --> 01:19:58.415
and I know his brothers!

01:19:59.060 --> 01:20:02.894
I told you what I know so you could
save his arse, huh?

01:20:03.131 --> 01:20:06.498
But no, he's just another paddy
to you and your big boys, isn't he?

01:20:07.068 --> 01:20:09.798
You know what? Get the fuck out
of my country.

01:20:18.680 --> 01:20:21.410
we all know
the lRA aren't terrorists.

01:20:21.983 --> 01:20:24.349
The lRA are freedom fighters.

01:20:28.156 --> 01:20:30.522
Rise up for our help, oh, Lord!

01:20:30.625 --> 01:20:34.152
Strike down our enemies before us.

01:20:35.831 --> 01:20:39.267
An eyewitness maintains one of
the men pleaded for his life...

01:20:39.301 --> 01:20:40.768
before he was shot.

01:20:41.469 --> 01:20:44.063
This brings to eight the number
of IRA members...

01:20:44.105 --> 01:20:46.437
who have been killed
in the last three months.

01:20:58.753 --> 01:21:01.221
Right, stop here.
Right, remember, lads...

01:21:01.289 --> 01:21:04.417
single shots to head and the body.
No fucking around, okay?

01:21:04.492 --> 01:21:05.390
Away you go.

01:21:13.869 --> 01:21:16.463
-well, how's the kid?
-He's grown.

01:21:17.138 --> 01:21:19.129
-They tend to do that.
-Yeah.

01:21:29.050 --> 01:21:30.642
-Fuck it!
-well?

01:21:30.685 --> 01:21:32.653
-The fucker wouldn't go down.
-Drive.

01:21:33.889 --> 01:21:35.322
-This wee girl was watching.
-Huh?

01:21:37.058 --> 01:21:39.925
we were wearing the balaclavas, for
Christ's sake. She wouldn't make us.

01:21:39.995 --> 01:21:41.394
Right. Here, get them shirts off.

01:21:43.331 --> 01:21:46.357
I want you to take the car up
to Hightown Road. Burn it, okay?

01:21:47.335 --> 01:21:50.429
-Did we actually get what we came for?
-Saturday, 28th of March.

01:21:51.973 --> 01:21:53.998
At least something went fucking right.

01:22:16.531 --> 01:22:19.159
I've not really been sleeping.

01:22:20.268 --> 01:22:22.668
That's why God invented sleeping pills.

01:22:23.638 --> 01:22:25.230
I take it you've reconsidered?

01:22:27.709 --> 01:22:30.111
-The hit on Park Street was...
-Ray?

01:22:30.111 --> 01:22:37.483
Aye, and Johnny. And a wee girl
saw the whole fucking thing.

01:22:37.585 --> 01:22:38.813
Yeah. Seven years old.

01:22:39.821 --> 01:22:43.279
She was right next to her daddy.
Got covered in his blood, I'm told.

01:22:44.025 --> 01:22:45.253
I've got a son...

01:22:45.293 --> 01:22:48.456
and there's nobody deserves to grow up
with that picture in their mind.

01:22:51.299 --> 01:22:53.494
Fergus, they didn't give me any
warning about this one.

01:22:53.601 --> 01:22:55.592
I'm starting to, you know,
think that they're onto me.

01:22:58.139 --> 01:23:00.266
You wouldn't be here if they
were onto you.

01:23:00.408 --> 01:23:02.308
I've not got a good feeling about it.

01:23:03.778 --> 01:23:06.212
-My car's definitely marked, right?
-Yeah, of course.

01:23:06.781 --> 01:23:09.375
Go home.
Hug your wife and baby.

01:23:16.257 --> 01:23:21.251
The pub job's going on the 28th.
That's all I've got.

01:23:24.165 --> 01:23:25.757
well, you did well.

01:23:30.171 --> 01:23:30.967
Aye.

01:23:40.181 --> 01:23:42.012
Make sure you check the timer.

01:23:42.350 --> 01:23:44.443
That way it doesn't blow up
in your face.

01:23:45.286 --> 01:23:47.550
It's going to blow up
the whole city, man.

01:23:48.890 --> 01:23:52.417
It seems like whenever
you're around, nothing blows up.

01:23:59.200 --> 01:24:00.360
You want
to shut the door for me?

01:24:01.102 --> 01:24:03.195
Yeah, you give it a good kick.
Good man.

01:24:03.838 --> 01:24:05.206
There you go.

01:24:05.206 --> 01:24:08.403
what'd we get Mummy?
we've got fish and chips, didn't we?

01:24:08.476 --> 01:24:11.445
Straight out the deep fat
fryer, we caught this, me and Patrick.

01:24:12.380 --> 01:24:14.143
All right, let's get some food.

01:24:15.383 --> 01:24:19.820
Your friends Mickey and Grace
dropped by.

01:24:21.489 --> 01:24:25.687
They went on about the new house,
the fridge, the cooker.

01:24:26.795 --> 01:24:29.195
They were extremely interested
in the new TV.

01:24:30.331 --> 01:24:32.765
It's fine. Honestly, I think
it's nothing.

01:24:33.334 --> 01:24:35.962
-They trust me. It's fine.
-we have a child, Martin.

01:24:36.704 --> 01:24:40.663
For his sake, I'd leave,
but I'm pregnant.

01:24:43.344 --> 01:24:44.811
where am I going to go?

01:24:47.715 --> 01:24:49.876
Look, let's get married.
I want to get married. Do you?

01:24:49.951 --> 01:24:51.748
I do. Let's get married, please?
Come on.

01:24:51.853 --> 01:24:53.514
-why?
-why get married?

01:24:53.588 --> 01:24:56.489
what do you mean, "why?"
Because I love you, that's why.

01:24:57.859 --> 01:24:58.553
Love?

01:25:00.428 --> 01:25:04.057
Every time you leave, I wonder if
it's the last time I'll see you alive.

01:25:04.099 --> 01:25:05.191
I have nightmares!

01:25:05.733 --> 01:25:08.361
The neighbours are afraid of you,
and you wear that like a medal.

01:25:08.369 --> 01:25:11.133
I heard you were palling with
the RA nutters!

01:25:11.172 --> 01:25:13.697
Are you? Are you?

01:25:15.210 --> 01:25:18.737
what exactly does the daddy
of our wee boy do for "the cause"?

01:25:41.870 --> 01:25:44.202
Marty, see you for
a couple minutes, son?

01:25:44.772 --> 01:25:46.967
-Mickey...
-Marty will debrief you later.

01:25:56.784 --> 01:25:58.274
Looks like we're all set.

01:25:59.587 --> 01:26:02.181
Here's a present.
It's from Mickey.

01:26:02.957 --> 01:26:06.552
He wants you to keep it close by.
You know how he worries.

01:26:06.594 --> 01:26:10.121
Aye. This is going to make you famous.

01:26:11.232 --> 01:26:15.293
By the way, it's only me
and you know the exact location.

01:26:16.337 --> 01:26:17.099
Aye.

01:26:45.533 --> 01:26:47.000
Info finally confirmed.

01:26:48.002 --> 01:26:51.199
Every Saturday, the prison wardens
play a football match.

01:26:51.906 --> 01:26:53.931
Locations are kept top secret.

01:26:55.543 --> 01:26:58.637
Now, next Saturday, March 28th,
after the Semis...

01:26:59.280 --> 01:27:01.578
they'll be drinking in the whale Pub.

01:27:01.649 --> 01:27:02.843
So we have a week.

01:27:04.485 --> 01:27:06.544
This is the big one.
Did you give her the gun?

01:27:06.554 --> 01:27:09.819
Yes. Look, tonight we do a test run.

01:27:09.924 --> 01:27:12.859
we check the place out,
we finalize details. No weapons.

01:27:12.927 --> 01:27:17.057
Look, if anything happens, they will
definitely know that it was me who told.

01:27:17.131 --> 01:27:18.428
Go on the recce tonight.

01:27:18.499 --> 01:27:21.593
we won't do anything till next
Saturday. That's when we grab them...

01:27:22.403 --> 01:27:25.099
armed and loaded, and when all the
shit goes down...

01:27:25.240 --> 01:27:28.409
you walk into one of our
secured vehicles.

01:27:28.409 --> 01:27:29.637
we'll pull your family out.

01:27:30.979 --> 01:27:33.539
Don't tell Lara anything.
A slip could be costly.

01:27:36.951 --> 01:27:38.316
She's pregnant again.

01:27:42.323 --> 01:27:46.259
Congratulations. I won't let anything
happen to you or your family.

01:27:51.899 --> 01:27:53.230
Ml5 just called me.

01:27:54.269 --> 01:27:56.794
-Of course you told them to fuck off.
-It's done.

01:27:59.540 --> 01:28:02.065
-The pub job?
-They're running it now.

01:28:04.379 --> 01:28:05.676
what about my source?

01:28:07.548 --> 01:28:12.451
A good handler manages the source.
He doesn't let the source manage him.

01:28:13.187 --> 01:28:14.916
He's not your source anymore.

01:28:18.559 --> 01:28:22.051
It's shit like this that ends careers,
so walk away.

01:28:32.473 --> 01:28:34.407
well, lads, for security purposes...

01:28:34.475 --> 01:28:38.468
most of you are hearing this
for the first time, so pay attention.

01:28:39.113 --> 01:28:41.843
It's your lives that's at risk
here, okay?

01:28:42.950 --> 01:28:44.247
Martin, it's all yours.

01:28:45.386 --> 01:28:47.354
Okay, we'll have two AKs in
the getaway car.

01:28:47.422 --> 01:28:49.356
All right, escape routes
are on your maps.

01:28:50.591 --> 01:28:53.492
-How many rounds we got?
-About 1 89.

01:28:54.495 --> 01:28:57.328
Two mags for each of the AKs.
Spares are in the getaway car.

01:28:57.765 --> 01:29:00.063
-why, do you think that's enough?
-Aye.

01:29:00.968 --> 01:29:03.869
Tonight is a dry run.
we make sure our plan is good to go.

01:29:03.905 --> 01:29:06.499
Next Saturday, on the 28th,
it's for real.

01:29:06.507 --> 01:29:10.603
Sean, Kieran, you go in the side door.
Grace, we'll go in the front.

01:29:10.678 --> 01:29:11.838
Check all exits.

01:29:11.946 --> 01:29:13.106
A wee bottle of Guinness.

01:29:13.147 --> 01:29:15.581
Johnny, stay with the getaway car.

01:29:16.417 --> 01:29:18.408
I'll go inside, I'll keep watch on
the front door.

01:29:18.453 --> 01:29:20.216
Get yourselves a drink,
do what you've got to do...

01:29:20.355 --> 01:29:22.448
but don't leave any fingerprints.

01:29:23.691 --> 01:29:24.817
Keep the change.

01:30:09.670 --> 01:30:13.197
Aye. Ease up, man.
For fuck's sake.

01:30:20.681 --> 01:30:21.943
You got the time?

01:30:24.952 --> 01:30:26.476
Code green.
Code green.

01:30:39.767 --> 01:30:43.430
Shit! You're a dead man!
You're a dead man!

01:30:44.472 --> 01:30:46.872
You fucking bastard, you.

01:30:48.609 --> 01:30:49.906
You're a fucking tout!

01:30:51.512 --> 01:30:53.480
You fucking bastard.
I'm going to kill you!

01:30:59.987 --> 01:31:01.614
we've got you now, bitch!

01:31:17.638 --> 01:31:18.502
Hello?

01:31:19.807 --> 01:31:21.001
Lara? Lara, it's me.

01:31:21.108 --> 01:31:22.939
Oh, God. Martin...

01:31:23.544 --> 01:31:25.273
Listen to me.
Listen to me, okay?

01:31:25.379 --> 01:31:29.179
I need you to kiss Patrick good night
for me, okay?

01:31:33.354 --> 01:31:34.821
we're going to be all right.

01:31:35.189 --> 01:31:36.781
I'm going to go to my mommy's.

01:31:38.759 --> 01:31:40.192
I'm so sorry.

01:31:41.662 --> 01:31:42.629
Martin?

01:31:43.297 --> 01:31:44.195
Aye.

01:31:44.665 --> 01:31:46.462
I got a question for you.

01:31:46.834 --> 01:31:48.062
what's that?

01:31:50.671 --> 01:31:51.968
will you marry me?

01:31:52.773 --> 01:31:53.569
Aye.

01:31:54.609 --> 01:31:57.703
You promise?
So we're married?

01:31:58.579 --> 01:31:59.705
Yeah, we're married.

01:32:03.050 --> 01:32:06.986
Great.
we are man and wife.

01:32:09.423 --> 01:32:10.253
I love you.

01:32:13.694 --> 01:32:17.562
I love you, too.
I love you, and I love Patrick, okay?

01:32:18.132 --> 01:32:20.657
-But you've got to get out.
-what's that?

01:32:37.885 --> 01:32:39.785
-So where is he?
-How the fuck do I know?

01:32:40.621 --> 01:32:43.283
Under the circumstances, I think
it's a pretty fair question.

01:32:43.357 --> 01:32:44.824
Did you compromise the operation?

01:32:44.892 --> 01:32:47.554
Oh, so that's it, is it?
That's how this is going to go down?

01:32:47.628 --> 01:32:50.028
Ml5 step in, screw up,
and I get to eat the bullshit?

01:32:53.034 --> 01:32:54.934
It's a big picture thing.

01:32:57.705 --> 01:32:59.866
It was supposed to be an easy bait
and switch...

01:33:00.374 --> 01:33:02.296
and your boy shouldn't have
walked out of there but he did...

01:33:02.310 --> 01:33:04.175
and now there's a mess to clean up.

01:33:07.114 --> 01:33:10.675
Don't be forgetting,
you're one of the good guys.

01:33:13.220 --> 01:33:14.983
-A man of the law.
-Since when?

01:33:16.490 --> 01:33:18.720
Since when did this
become about the law?

01:33:58.165 --> 01:33:59.723
what the hell happened to you?

01:34:00.801 --> 01:34:02.701
Me and Lara had a fight.

01:34:03.971 --> 01:34:05.268
Oh, Marty...

01:34:08.809 --> 01:34:09.537
Ma, no.

01:34:11.712 --> 01:34:12.303
Hello?

01:34:12.413 --> 01:34:13.641
Hello, is Martin there?

01:34:13.714 --> 01:34:15.306
No, I haven't seen him.

01:34:15.416 --> 01:34:17.247
-Tell him it's Fergus calling.
-Fergus?

01:34:17.818 --> 01:34:18.978
Give me the phone.

01:34:19.253 --> 01:34:21.380
You set me up, man,
you lying bastard!

01:34:21.455 --> 01:34:23.685
Look, it had nothing to do with me.
I'll be there in 20.

01:34:23.724 --> 01:34:25.191
I'm your only chance now.

01:34:27.995 --> 01:34:30.657
-Marty, what's going on?
-It's fine, Ma.

01:34:30.731 --> 01:34:32.426
-T ell me!
-Listen, it's all right.

01:34:37.171 --> 01:34:38.900
He's a tout, Mrs. McGartland.

01:34:39.473 --> 01:34:42.931
There's no way that's true.
Marty?

01:34:48.949 --> 01:34:51.645
The Special Branch
don't want him anymore.

01:34:53.020 --> 01:34:54.612
-Connie!
-Connie, no!

01:34:55.956 --> 01:34:57.719
No! No!

01:34:58.159 --> 01:34:59.956
If you leave them, look,
I'll go with you.

01:35:00.027 --> 01:35:02.222
Okay, you leave my family, please.

01:35:03.330 --> 01:35:05.321
Ma... Ma, listen to me.
I'll be fine.

01:35:05.433 --> 01:35:07.833
I'll be back in two hours.
Okay? Two hours.

01:35:09.270 --> 01:35:11.329
Let go of me!
Let go of me!

01:35:11.439 --> 01:35:13.134
Get off him!
Get off him!

01:35:14.508 --> 01:35:15.634
Oh, Ma...

01:35:15.976 --> 01:35:17.307
Are you all right?

01:35:18.713 --> 01:35:19.338
Christ.

01:35:20.347 --> 01:35:21.644
Oh, Christ!

01:35:30.991 --> 01:35:31.753
Yeah.

01:35:33.527 --> 01:35:36.928
Jesus. Fine.
we're not going anywhere.

01:35:36.997 --> 01:35:38.294
I'm just getting a bath.

01:35:42.336 --> 01:35:44.304
They won't be here for another hour.

01:35:53.180 --> 01:35:56.013
If it was up to me, you wouldn't
be seeing the end of that hour.

01:36:03.090 --> 01:36:06.548
Piece of shit.
Get his feet. Come on.

01:36:14.769 --> 01:36:17.237
Oh, shit. Ow, fuck!

01:36:21.408 --> 01:36:22.670
where's Martin, then?

01:36:25.279 --> 01:36:27.110
You going
to let them kill your mate?

01:36:27.515 --> 01:36:28.982
He's not my mate.

01:36:29.416 --> 01:36:31.118
You ever wonder why you're
not behind bars...

01:36:31.118 --> 01:36:33.746
when we've been all over you
for the past two years?

01:36:34.955 --> 01:36:36.286
Your mate, Martin.

01:36:41.328 --> 01:36:44.354
I hear the Special Branch
have lost interest in you.

01:36:44.431 --> 01:36:47.457
well, then, that makes me unofficial.

01:36:47.902 --> 01:36:49.927
New rules.
You get to live if he lives.

01:36:54.542 --> 01:36:55.941
Broom Park.

01:36:56.811 --> 01:36:59.075
Broom Park,
you fucking bastard!

01:37:16.330 --> 01:37:18.890
Yeah, this is a message
from John Smith, IRA.

01:37:19.466 --> 01:37:22.196
There's a bomb.
A lot of Samaritans will die.

01:37:22.269 --> 01:37:23.133
Broom Park.

01:37:23.270 --> 01:37:24.430
what is the password?

01:37:25.005 --> 01:37:25.835
Carry Gold.

01:37:30.644 --> 01:37:31.702
what do you have?

01:37:31.846 --> 01:37:34.014
we need to be able to question him.
Bring him in here.

01:37:34.014 --> 01:37:34.844
Come on.

01:37:37.551 --> 01:37:38.677
Over there.

01:37:55.035 --> 01:37:57.401
Fucking peelers like flies on shit.

01:38:04.411 --> 01:38:06.038
You going to tell me what you did?

01:38:29.169 --> 01:38:32.229
I'm pretty sure the lRA is holding
my top boy somewhere in there.

01:38:32.339 --> 01:38:34.136
Funny coincidence, that we're looking
for a bomb...

01:38:34.174 --> 01:38:36.165
in the same place that
your source is being held.

01:38:36.243 --> 01:38:36.971
Thomas...

01:38:37.077 --> 01:38:39.910
Oh, great delay tactic. Pretty
much locked the place down.

01:38:40.547 --> 01:38:41.377
Move out!

01:38:41.448 --> 01:38:43.382
Come on, man, who are you
taking orders from?

01:38:44.184 --> 01:38:45.947
Look, I'm just trying to make it
to retirement.

01:38:45.986 --> 01:38:47.544
Oh, fuck it, then. Fuck it.

01:38:47.688 --> 01:38:49.019
Some stunt.

01:38:49.089 --> 01:38:49.987
Move out!

01:39:02.002 --> 01:39:03.469
Fuck, come on!

01:39:16.483 --> 01:39:18.747
You're going to talk, Marty,
you know that.

01:39:20.854 --> 01:39:22.014
You know that?

01:39:26.694 --> 01:39:28.457
Keep it shut right now, right?

01:39:29.663 --> 01:39:30.527
Get it.

01:39:36.971 --> 01:39:39.439
-what are you doing here?
-He was my mate.

01:39:39.506 --> 01:39:41.997
-You're not authorized, Sean...
-I want to hear him fucking say it!

01:39:42.042 --> 01:39:43.737
-Sean, you're not authorized...
-Say it!

01:39:44.411 --> 01:39:46.313
Get out, Sean!
This is an army order.

01:39:46.313 --> 01:39:48.577
I'm your senior officer.
Get out!

01:39:49.516 --> 01:39:51.211
Sean, are you deaf?
Get out!

01:39:52.252 --> 01:39:54.720
You'll bring the peelers to the fucking
door if you're not careful...

01:39:54.788 --> 01:39:57.086
Shut up! I want to fucking
hear him say it!

01:39:57.157 --> 01:39:58.055
Hey!

01:40:10.137 --> 01:40:11.331
Get an ambulance, now!

01:40:20.647 --> 01:40:22.877
He's a peeler.
we have no orders for this.

01:40:35.562 --> 01:40:36.893
Jesus Christ.

01:40:39.466 --> 01:40:41.127
Okay, what happened?

01:40:48.108 --> 01:40:49.507
Get him back.

01:41:12.132 --> 01:41:14.362
-Take him to City Hospital.
-The Royal's closer.

01:41:14.401 --> 01:41:17.029
He won't live if we take him there.
Take him to the City.

01:41:19.406 --> 01:41:21.340
Get alongside him.
Get alongside him!

01:41:40.094 --> 01:41:42.289
Right up Jackson Street!
Jackson Street!

01:41:54.108 --> 01:41:55.405
Keep going and ram him.

01:42:13.760 --> 01:42:14.624
Fuck him!

01:42:22.936 --> 01:42:24.631
Shit! Shit!

01:42:29.009 --> 01:42:30.169
watch the door!

01:42:37.618 --> 01:42:40.314
So, Robbie, I hear the shit's
going down at Special Branch?

01:42:40.320 --> 01:42:43.255
Bloody hell.
what is the matter with you?

01:42:44.024 --> 01:42:48.393
why is the kid still breathing?
was it not a simple request?

01:42:48.896 --> 01:42:50.386
If it was, you'd have done
it yourselves.

01:42:50.464 --> 01:42:51.863
-Fuck off.
-You asked.

01:42:53.433 --> 01:42:54.866
Yeah, well, clean it up.

01:43:06.613 --> 01:43:09.707
If the RUC don't protect him,
Ml5 will leave him exposed...

01:43:09.816 --> 01:43:10.976
a gift to the lRA...

01:43:11.018 --> 01:43:13.953
a bait and switch to deflect
attention from a plant higher up.

01:43:14.021 --> 01:43:16.285
-what's your stake in this?
-He was my operative.

01:43:17.824 --> 01:43:18.722
Shit...

01:43:20.227 --> 01:43:22.491
Look, there's no way I can get
involved in this, for fuck's sake.

01:43:22.529 --> 01:43:25.498
well, how about I go to the press,
and we debate this in public?

01:43:25.632 --> 01:43:27.725
You won't live long enough
to do that, and you know it.

01:43:27.801 --> 01:43:31.237
Martin. That's his name.
Martin.

01:43:34.474 --> 01:43:39.502
He saved, I'd guess, 50 soldiers,
RUC officers, prison wardens.

01:43:39.546 --> 01:43:42.435
Ml5 turns him into a bargaining chip.
He has a girlfriend...

01:43:42.482 --> 01:43:44.279
a son, and another baby on the way.

01:43:47.988 --> 01:43:48.784
Look...

01:43:49.790 --> 01:43:52.987
we uphold the law and break
the law in the name of the law.

01:43:53.026 --> 01:43:53.993
Is that why you signed up?

01:43:54.061 --> 01:43:57.326
There isn't a day goes by when I don't
fulfil my oath to serve this community.

01:43:57.397 --> 01:43:58.421
I know.

01:43:59.233 --> 01:44:02.066
Shit... why me?

01:44:41.441 --> 01:44:45.502
You f...
You fuck...

01:44:52.352 --> 01:44:55.446
-where's Lara and the boy?
-They're at her mum's.

01:44:59.459 --> 01:45:02.257
How long have I been out?

01:45:03.730 --> 01:45:05.755
Long enough for
the dust to settle.

01:45:10.103 --> 01:45:11.866
You deserted me.

01:45:15.075 --> 01:45:17.908
well, like it or not,
I'm your only friend right now.

01:45:21.114 --> 01:45:22.809
My real name's Dean.

01:45:24.384 --> 01:45:27.785
But you can keep calling me Fergus.
The name's grown on me.

01:45:30.824 --> 01:45:31.916
Is he okay?

01:45:34.961 --> 01:45:35.893
He's okay, yeah.

01:45:40.767 --> 01:45:43.429
-His wife's here to see him.
-He hasn't got a wife.

01:45:44.504 --> 01:45:47.371
-where's the RUC officer?
-I don't know where he is.

01:45:47.441 --> 01:45:48.635
Did you tell her what room he's in?

01:45:54.014 --> 01:45:55.504
This is against my orders.

01:45:55.615 --> 01:45:57.082
well, he won't last the night
if he stops here.

01:45:57.617 --> 01:46:01.109
He has a deep internal cut,
a fractured jaw, a severe concussion...

01:46:01.154 --> 01:46:02.553
and several broken ribs.

01:46:02.622 --> 01:46:04.487
Just pray this
is a nine-lives situation.

01:46:40.093 --> 01:46:42.391
So this is pretty cozy
for a safe house.

01:46:43.196 --> 01:46:44.322
It's my house.

01:46:58.211 --> 01:47:02.875
So, Dean,
I hope you have a plan.

01:47:04.050 --> 01:47:06.416
well, Lara still doesn't
know you're alive.

01:47:07.754 --> 01:47:10.382
I've negotiated a deal
with Scotland Yard.

01:47:16.596 --> 01:47:17.563
Call Lara.

01:47:18.432 --> 01:47:20.832
See if she'll like the idea
of getting married in Scotland.

01:47:25.872 --> 01:47:28.500
You know, you look me in the eye,
okay...

01:47:29.242 --> 01:47:31.972
and you tell me what kind
of life you think she'd have.

01:47:33.180 --> 01:47:35.148
No hope, no friends, no community.

01:47:35.949 --> 01:47:39.783
Always looking over our shoulder,
scared to death for them kids.

01:47:42.289 --> 01:47:43.517
I can't do it.

01:47:45.725 --> 01:47:47.556
I really can't do it.
I won't do it.

01:48:01.641 --> 01:48:03.871
You know, I thought
I was saving lives.

01:48:05.111 --> 01:48:06.738
A superhero.

01:48:32.772 --> 01:48:34.399
Do you ever see your kid?

01:48:34.508 --> 01:48:38.000
He's... he's got a lot going on
right now.

01:49:01.134 --> 01:49:02.658
Okay, let's go.

01:49:26.459 --> 01:49:28.791
Oh, my God.
Help...

01:49:30.063 --> 01:49:30.791
Help!

01:49:31.565 --> 01:49:32.759
Call an ambulance!

01:49:35.735 --> 01:49:38.067
Stay awake.
Help is coming.

01:49:38.171 --> 01:49:40.639
Do you have family?
who should I call?

01:49:41.908 --> 01:49:44.672
Dean. Dean McTear.
Dean McTear.

01:49:45.512 --> 01:49:49.972
-He's family?
-Yeah. Dean McTear.

